Heat oil in large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat until hot. Add potatoes; cover and cook 8 to 10 minutes or until potatoes are lightly browned, turning occasionally. Meanwhile remove pot roast from package; set aside. Transfer gravy to medium bowl; stir in salsa, chipotle pepper and adobo sauce. Cut pot roast into 1-inch pieces. Add beef and salsa mixture to skillet; mix well. Cover and cook over medium heat 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Sprinkle with cheese; cook, covered, 1 to 2 minutes or until cheese is melted.